      • testFROMisRelativeToMappingLocation2

        public void testFROMisRelativeToMappingLocation2()
                                          throws java.io.IOException
        This isn't quite legal. An IRI of the form "file:relative/path/to/file" is not valid, even though it appears to work here. Jena correctly prints out a warning. We leave the test here for now, but this is not really a good idea. ("file:///absolute/path/to/file" is fine, as is "relative/path/to/file".)
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
